Sentencas: The feasibility of producing solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) which could be rapidly heated to operating temperature was investigated.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of small diameter tubular solid oxide fuel cells for rapid start-up

Sentencas: Small diameter (2.4 mm) 3 and 8 mol% yttria-stabilised zirconia (YSZ) tubes were used both as the electrolyte and the cell support tube.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of small diameter tubular solid oxide fuel cells for rapid start-up

Sentencas: Cells were prepared by winding with pure silver, Ni80/Cr20 and Nimonic 90 wires over lanthanum-strontium-manganite (LSM) cathodes.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of small diameter tubular solid oxide fuel cells for rapid start-up

Sentencas: Specific power outputs of up to 250 mA/cm(2) at 900 degrees C, 0.7 V were achieved in silver wound cells with 5 mm long cathodes.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of small diameter tubular solid oxide fuel cells for rapid start-up

Sentencas: Longer cathodes produced progressively lower specific outputs.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of small diameter tubular solid oxide fuel cells for rapid start-up

Sentencas: This was attributed to increasing cathode and winding resistance with length.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of small diameter tubular solid oxide fuel cells for rapid start-up

Sentencas: The base metal windings achieved up to 80% of the performance of a similar length cell wound with pure silver wire.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of small diameter tubular solid oxide fuel cells for rapid start-up

Sentencas: Silver wound cells were successfully cycled between 200 and 900 degrees C at an average 25 degrees C/min (peak 100 degrees C/min) over 50 cycles with no degradation due to the thermal cycling.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of small diameter tubular solid oxide fuel cells for rapid start-up

Sentencas: Degradation in cells wound with base metals was attributable to the increase in contact resistance found between the cathode and the wire with time.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of small diameter tubular solid oxide fuel cells for rapid start-up
